	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f106027473665452>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: Question</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Aug 7th 12:54 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>311 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.18]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Unlike other abilities, not all skills are equal when it comes to a SHD.<br><br>Alteration is pretty much the run away winner in terms of the sheer number of SHD spells (lifetaps, hell, almost everything... =p) that use that skill.&nbsp;&nbsp;You will most likely have little trouble keeping this skill maxxed out each level.<br><br>Conjuration is probably next and you will cast many of these spells also (snare, etc.).  You will most likely have little trouble keeping this skill maxxed out.<br><br>Abjuration is probably next.  Despite the fact that it doesnt have a similar number of SHD spells that use this skill, it *IS* very important to keep this skill up, particularly after level 30.  The reason for this is the FD is abjuration and once you get this ability, you will use it often and for the rest of your SHD career.<br><br>Divination is probably next.  Invising and such is important, but just not to the same degree as the previous 3.  Its somewhat easy to max this out, however, because you will invis so often.  If maxing this skill out is a concern, just practice invis to undead, which SHD get at lvl 9.<br><br>Evocation is perhaps the most pathetic skill we need to max.  Due to the fact that so few SHD spells actually use this skill, its generally hard to max this out.  Dont stress, however, as this skill borders on pathetic and seems to be becoming more worthless now that Scythe of Innoruuk (&quot;SoI&quot;) might be coming out.  Evocation is pretty much only for undead nukes (/puke), which few seem to use consistently and, which makes it even more lame, SoI, which is an upgrade, is conjuration.  At the moment, you can almost ignore evocation.  I dont see how it will make much difference at all nowadays.<br><br>I never found BW or Hide that useful.  Im sure they are, but just never fancied me all that much.  They seem to be more useful at lower levels then higher levels.  I can say confidently that seldom do I see these skills being performed on a consistent basis in PoP.<br><br>Luna  <br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Aug  7 12:53:10 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
